  }, "Omar Wasow"), ":"), mdx("p", null, "That's right. That's right. That's right. What I was trying to champion with some of my work was the internet as a supper club, exactly as you're saying, not as a superhighway. It's also important to appreciate that if we think about some of the underlying technology, we go to a webpage. This was fundamentally the both technical and conceptual metaphor was books, and so you really had to hack it to make it social."), mdx("p", null, mdx("em", {
