    parentName: "p"
  }, "Ethan Zuckerman"), ":"), mdx("p", null, "At that point, it's the fourth-largest social network on the web. It's a big deal. I mean Facebook has formed then. MySpace is out there. Why was this so successful and why was that the right time to step back from it?"), mdx("p", null, mdx("em", {
    parentName: "p"
  }, "Omar Wasow"), ":"), mdx("p", null, "Yeah. I mean, I think it's helpful to just underline a couple of points. For people who've come of age with Facebook as the dominant site or Facebook and Twitter and a couple of others, that this is an era where it's churning. We've got lots of different sites coming and going. You mentioned Tripod and there was one called The Globe that came and went in the early 2000s. Even SixDegrees.com if we want to go way back."), mdx("p", null, mdx("em", {
