  }, "Ethan Zuckerman:")), mdx("p", null, "So step one and this is a normative shift, right? Step one of this is norms and attitudes. Is there any part of the world where you see law sort of catching up with this?"), mdx("p", null, mdx("em", {
    parentName: "p"
  }, "Eliza Sorensen:")), mdx("p", null, "So I think New Zealand is a good place in general, but they do not apply their decriminalization to immigrants. Which is a big problem and causes lots of hurt among that community. They're Five Eyes country, so they have some very crappy laws already and especially around classification. Because we all borrow from each other. Unfortunately, I don't think there's a country in Europe that's doing it well. Germany is mostly parsecs, however, due to the pandemic we're seeing the rhetoric of disease spread is come back up. Like, the things that we saw during the plague."), mdx("p", null, mdx("em", {
