  }, "Ethan Zuckerman:")), mdx("p", null, "What's very challenging about Solid for people to sort of understand is it's really a very different paradigm than we're used to. We're sort of used to this notion that a service is a place and that place has certain data about us and we have frankly no rights to retrieve that data, right?"), mdx("p", null, "Facebook sort of tosses us a bone and we can appeal to download our historic Facebook transactions. Twitter has the ability to get the Twitter archive, but that's very different from the model that you're talking about, where in theory, you could simply revoke an application's permissions to work with your data. You could pull things back, even after having agreed to something."), mdx("p", null, "Help me understand the identity piece of things, which sounds like it's become a much more visible part of the Solid universe since the last time I talked with Sir Tim about this. How do identities work in this space? How do I find you in a Solid world?"), mdx("p", null, mdx("em", {
