    parentName: "p"
  }, "Julia Angwin:")), mdx("p", null, "Oh, there's a lot of ways it could go that aren't hopeful, but I'll focus on a hopeful scenario. I think that there is a possibility and this will see in Pollyanna, but there is a possibility that the fact that we have chosen to encode our biases, the way that Amazon encoded theirs in this machine learning system, makes them more inspectable and more fixable. And so Amazon was probably always a really sexist place and there maybe no one had any sort of understanding of how that came to be and they could tune the dial. You can actually, now that it's a dial, you can turn the dial and to be like, okay, let's be less sexist. Now is the world going to make those choices? Is Amazon going to make those choices? I don't know. But I have a small bit of hope in me that we could redress so many of the inequities in our society because by putting them into technology, we have given ourselves levers and we could move those levers."), mdx("p", null, mdx("em", {
